# Dynamic Blog & Admin Dashboard Implementation

We will upgrade the static Astrologer blog to a fully dynamic system using **Firebase**. This means you (or the astrologer) can log into a secure Admin Dashboard on the website, write blog posts, add tags, and publish them. The site will automatically fetch from the database to display them.

## User Action Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To proceed, you will briefly need to act as the webmaster and create a free database. 
> 1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/).
> 2. Create a new project.
> 3. Enable **Firestore Database** (start in Test Mode for now).
> 4. Go to Project Settings and add a Web App to get your **Firebase Configuration Object** (the `apiKey`, `projectId`, etc.). You will need to provide this to me so I can connect the website to it.

